        <h2>Questions, answered.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq reveal">
      <details>
        <summary>Why does live streaming build more trust than pre-recorded video?</summary>
        <p>It lets viewers ask questions, react, and interact with a brand as things happen, creating an authenticity that scripted, pre-recorded video can't replicate.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>When should a brand go live?</summary>
        <p>Good moments include product launches, live Q&As or AMAs, company milestones, event broadcasting, and employee spotlights or culture moments.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How can a brand repurpose a live stream after it ends?</summary>
        <p>A single live stream can be cut into shorter clips, quote graphics, blog posts, and highlight reels, extending its value well beyond the live moment.</p>
      </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

